==English==

===Adjective===
'''angry''' (''comparative:'' [[angrier]], ''superlative:'' [[angriest]])
# Irritated, in a temper; displaying [[anger]].
#:''An angry mob started looting the warehouse.''
# (said about a wound or a rash) Inflamed and painful
#:''The broken glass left two angry cuts across my arm.''
# (literary use) (said about the sky or the sea) dark and stormy, menacing
#:''...nor dreads he the angry sea...'' (Horace, The Book of the Epodes, Ode II)
#: ''angry clouds racing across the sky''

